{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b03d06b2-5432-4284-a352-02b0c39722a0","content":"You're on **MSTest 3.8.2**, so here's the modern approach:\n\n### `TestContext` injection\nUse **constructor injection** — the legacy `public static TestContext TestContext { get; set; }` pattern is obsolete:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests\n{\n    private readonly TestContext _testContext;\n\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        _testContext = testContext;\n        // synchronous init goes here\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Async initialization\nConstructors can't be `async`, so use `[TestInitialize]` (per-test) or `[ClassInitialize]` (once per class):\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests\n{\n    private readonly TestContext _testContext;\n    private MyService _service;\n\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        _testContext = testContext;          // sync init\n    }\n\n    [ClassInitialize]\n    public static async Task Setup(TestContext context)\n    {\n        await SomeOneTimeSetupAsync();      // async class-level init\n    }\n\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task BeforeEach()\n    {\n        _service = await MyService.CreateAsync(); // async per-test init\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- Constructor → sync init + `TestContext` injection\n- `[TestInitialize]` → async per-test setup\n- `[ClassInitialize]` → async one-time setup (must be `static`, takes `TestContext` parameter)\n- `[ClassCleanup]` / `[TestCleanup]` for teardown (also support `async Task`)","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b88e55a2-501d-4090-b645-2f4e14a07d4b","outputTokens":407,"requestId":"1BC1:345713:524398:5D7911:6A03D787"},"id":"e6c31c5e-7f49-415b-af4c-c005b694a84b","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:44:49.133Z","parentId":"554fe8ad-1df2-4d9b-a433-9e04d171e0fa"}
